+
+Local parity evidence is materially stronger now. The render-level proof surfaces passed `35/35` frontend tests across faculty-profile, proof-summary, HoD, risk explorer, student shell, and sysadmin dashboard, and the committed backend route/service tests plus code inspection show that course leader, mentor, HoD, and student-shell drilldowns preserve the same run/checkpoint/student tuple when explicit playback is requested. The main new semantic contradiction is `C-021`: default faculty, HoD, and student proof slices can recurse into checkpoint-backed truth and then relabel it as `proof-run` while clearing checkpoint metadata.
